.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-proxmox-forget - Forget the saved Proxmox connection


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel proxmox forget [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Delete the saved Proxmox configuration file (proxmox.json).

.PP
The Control Center shows a Proxmox tab whenever a saved config exists, even if
this machine isn't a Proxmox host — the config may point at a remote server.
Forgetting the connection removes that file so the tab no longer appears.

.PP
The config file path is printed before deletion. Use --yes to skip the prompt.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for forget

.PP
\fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip the confirmation prompt.


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-proxmox(1)\fP
